---
title: One-Pan Spiced Turkey Lettuce Wraps with Tomato, Garlicky White Sauce, Almonds & Hot Sauce
description: We love a lettuce wrap. The crisp crunch, the perfectly cradled filling, and that satisfied-but-not-stuffed feeling afterward–what a perfect dinner idea! This version features fragrant, shawarma-spiced ground turkey scooped into lettuce leaves, topped with fresh tomato and tangy pickled onion, drizzled with creamy lemon-garlic sauce, and finished with crunchy almonds and hot sauce. It’s all ready in a quick 30 minutes—just keep napkins handy until you master your lettuce wrap-eating technique.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pan-spiced-turkey-lettuce-wraps-175977f2.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pan-spiced-turkey-lettuce-wraps-63cff79c340ebd192a07b1c6-b88f8861.pdf
cuisine: Middle East
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-spiced-turkey-lettuce-wraps-63cff79c340ebd192a07b1c6
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 550 kcal
  fat: 36 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 29 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 32 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 690 mg
---

Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @red onion{1}(halved and finely sliced); finely dice remaining half. Quarter @lemon{2}(quartered). Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves. Dice @tomato{1}(diced).

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, juice from one lemon, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, use juice from two lemons and 1 tsp sugar.) Microwave for ~{30%seconds}; set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

In a separate small #bowl{}, combine @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @garlic powder{3/4%tsp}, and a squeeze of lemon juice. (You'll use the rest of the garlic powder in the next step.) Season white sauce with salt and pepper.

> For 4 servings, use 1 1/2 tsp garlic powder instead of 3/4 tsp.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add diced onion and a pinch of salt; cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @ground turkey{10%oz}, @Shawarma spice blend{1%tbsp}, and remaining @garlic powder{1/4%tsp}; generously season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2} and @water{1/4%cup}, then reduce heat to medium low and simmer, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

> TIP: Stir in a splash of water near the end of cooking to make sure your turkey is nice and saucy!

Divide lettuce between plates. Fill with turkey, tomato, and as much pickled onion as you like (draining first).

Drizzle wraps with white sauce and as much @hot sauce{1%tsp} as you like; sprinkle with @sliced almonds{1/2%oz}. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.